<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf66c2ed8-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3704"><num value="3704">§ 3704.</num><heading> Coastwise trade vessels</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A segregated ballast tank, a crude oil washing system, or an inert gas system, required by this chapter or a regulation prescribed under this chapter, on a vessel entitled to engage in the coastwise trade under chapter 551 of this title shall be installed in the United States (except the trust territories). A vessel failing to comply with this section may not engage in the coastwise trade.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf66c2ed9-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/522">97 Stat. 522</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s15/16">Pub. L. 109–304, § 15(16)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1703">120 Stat. 1703</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
